<node id="World Athletics Federation">
  <data key="d0">World Athletics Federation</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">World Athletics, commonly known as the World Athletics Federation, is the international governing body for the sport of athletics. It oversees a wide range of athletic events and competitions, with a particular focus on the World Athletics Championships. The federation's primary responsibilities include validating world records to ensure that all achievements meet the necessary standards and criteria.

World Athletics plays a crucial role in setting rules and regulations for various disciplines such as track and field events, cross country running, road running, race walking, and more. By maintaining high standards of competition and record-keeping, World Athletics aims to promote the sport globally and foster fair play among athletes worldwide. The organization's efforts are directed towards ensuring that athletic competitions are conducted with integrity and transparency, thereby enhancing the credibility and appeal of the sport on an international scale.

The federation is responsible for overseeing the World Athletics Championship and validating world records. This involves meticulous record-keeping and adherence to strict criteria to ensure the authenticity and fairness of athletic achievements.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Athletics Federation is the governing body overseeing the World Athletics Championship and record validations.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Athletics Federation is the governing body overseeing the World Athletics Championship and record validations.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Athletics Federation is the governing body overseeing the World Athletics Championship and record validations.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Athletics Federation is the governing body overseeing the World Athletics Championship and record validations.</data>
