  <data key="d7">17.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The relation between A人員 (Personnel A) and B客戶 (Client B) is characterized by a range of maintenance activities. Personnel A plays a crucial role in maintaining Client B's systems, which involves various tasks such as handling maintenance duties and providing technical support. The involvement of Personnel A in these activities ensures that Client B's systems remain operational and well-maintained.

Personnel A is responsible for performing various engineering tasks in addition to maintenance duties. This relationship underscores the importance of Personnel A in supporting Client B through their expertise in system maintenance and technical assistance. Throughout a specified time frame, Personnel A has been actively involved in handling these maintenance tasks, ensuring that Client B's systems are well-maintained and operational.&lt;SEP&gt;A人員is involved in handling maintenance tasks for B客戶.&lt;SEP&gt;A人員is involved in the maintenance activities for B客戶.</data>
